ment due to public relations fallout claims of bad faithedit in june  nationwide was hit with an  million punitive damages award after a plaintiff proved the company strongarmed its own policyholder rather than negotiating in good faith to compensate plaintiff for the loss suffered in an automobile collision see alsoedit list of united states insurance companies referencesedit  newsroom  nationwidecom nationwidecom   wolf barnet d and charlie zimkus made in ohio the columbus dispatch oh  aug  b print  news resources  nationwidecom nationwidecom   fortune  fortune   httpfortunecombestcompanies   columbus childrens hospital becomes nationwide childrens hospital nationwidechildrensorg  retrieved    ryan nate september   nationwide to end sponsorship of nascars no  series usa today retrieved september     bruce kenny may   juniors sponsorship part of nationwide evolution nascar retrieved may     nationwide partners with jack hanna and the columbus zoo on wildlife conservation nationwide retrieved  november    crestbrook insurance expands into california more states to come   httpwwwhrcorgfilesassetsresourcesceifullpdf  tavis smiley hosts first on your side® tour stop with nationwide insurance black news retrieved  march    kass kelly nationwide insurance hits the ‘spot’ with enterprise collaboration platform simplycommunicate retrieved  february    buckley christian building a social platform with sharepoint and yammer at nationwide insurance cmswire retrieved  february    ask julie print share for ebusiness  channel strategy professionals case study nationwide insurance uses mobile to offer customers self service on the road forrester retrieved  february    a b scism leslie october   nationwide settles death benefits case the wallstreet journal online retrieved october     mercado daria may   insurance cops grill metlife nationwide on death benefits httpwwwinvestmentnewscom retrieved october    external link in publisher help  insurer hit with  mil punitive damages awa