mall company growth fund is an openended equity mutual fund launched and managed by nationwide fund advisors it is comanaged by brown capital management llc the fund invests in the public equity markets of the united states it seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors the fund primarily invests in growth stocks of smallcap companies having market capitalization of  million or less it employs fundamental analysis focusing on factors such as sustainable revenue growth adequate resources to establish and defend a viable product or service market and market share sufficient profitability to support longterm growth management skills and resources necessary to plan and execute a longterm growth plan to create its portfolio the fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the russell  growth index nationwide mutual funds  nationwide small company growth fund was formed on january   and is domiciled in the united states detailed description  continental drivesuite king of prussia pa united statesfounded in  phone  fax  mutualfundsnationwidecomiappmfscfundprofileactiontickernwsaxaudiencenf key executives for nationwide mutual funds  nationwide small company growth fund mr robert e hall portfolio manager mr keith alison lee portfolio manager age  mr kempton m ingersol portfolio manager mr damien l davis cfa managing director and portfolio manager mr andrew j fones portfolio manager compensation as of fiscal year  similar private companies by industry company name region visory llc united states  road partners llc united states t partners llc united states jumpcom inc united states  ontario inc united states recent private companies transactions typedate target no transactions available in the past  months request profile update   the information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market intelligence a division of sp global bloombergcom does not create or control the content for inquiries please